Description: Upper body sherd of Aeolian Wild Goat Style pottery dinos; white slip; interior: glazed streaky black; exterior: from top, hook maeander band above frieze of elongated tongues between pairs of lines; below, pendant roundel as filling ornament.
Producer name: Made by: The London Dinos Group
Curator's comments: Sherd belongs to the same vase as British Museum 1924,1201.1027 and 1032. For parallels, see Kerschner 2006, p. 124, fig. 15.
Bibliographic references: Lemos 1991 / Archaic Pottery of Chios. The Decorated Styles (p. 252, no. 397)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GK.34)
